To compile PyCorewar you need Python (>= 2.3.0 or higher) and a C-compiler.
To install it, run:

      python setup.py install

Type "./testsuite" to run the extensive testsuite.

The directory "Benchmarks" contains a little benchmark.

Windows
-------

If you happen to be sentenced to use Windows you can install Cygwin
(www.cygwin.com) to use PyCorewar. Make sure to install GCC, Python and
GNU Make. After that you can install it with:

      python setup.py install
